<p>I find cumbersome the default python syntax <code>val = a if cond else b</code>, so sometimes I do this:</p>

<pre><code>iif = lambda (cond, a, b): a if cond else b
# so I can then use it like:
val = iif(cond, a, b)
</code></pre>

<p>Of course, it has the downside of always evaluating both sides (a and b), but the syntax it's way clearer to me</p>
